# General Engineering Practices

## Code Splitting

- When a file becomes too long, split it into smaller, logically grouped files.
- When a function becomes too long, refactor it by splitting it into smaller, focused functions.

## Scalability and Maintainability

- After writing code, perform a deep reflection on its scalability and maintainability.
- Produce a 1-2 paragraph analysis of the code change based on these reflections.
- Suggest potential improvements or next steps as needed based on the analysis.
